M​uch of the overview material is good, but the  course is starting to show its age. Some of the resources are suffering from link rot and it is clear that it was conveived pre-pandemic, so some key developments are missing. If you have no famliarity with Quality, it is a great starting place, and let's be real healthcare is lagging other industries in this regard. It hits most of the important notes and the featured lecturers are true leaders, so it obviously has significant value.
